Released24 July 2006 (Update)
MembersYes
Map
Advanced data
Typerealm

The Dream World is the realm that players are required to go to in the quests Lunar Diplomacy, Dream Mentor and Dragon Slayer II. The only known means of access is through burning Soaked kindling or using a Potion of Shared Dreaming on the Ceremonial brazier located on Lunar Isle. The history of the player is contained within the book my life, which serves as an exit during Lunar Diplomacy.

A player enters the Dream World.

Monsters[edit | edit source]

The following monsters are encountered in the Dream World:

  • Me is only fought during Lunar Diplomacy
  • The Inadequacy during Dream Mentor
  • The Everlasting during Dream Mentor
  • The Untouchable during Dream Mentor
  • The Illusive during Dream Mentor
  • A Doubt during Dream Mentor
  • Robert the Strong during Dragon Slayer II

Trivia[edit | edit source]

A part of the Dream World, visible from the Mole Lair.
  • Parts of the Dream World (specifically, the parts visited during Dream Mentor and Dragon Slayer II) can be seen just east of the Falador Mole Lair if players have roofs toggled on in the Display Options.
  • Part of the Dream World is also visible from the first floor of the Stronghold of Security, right near the entrance.
  • The map of "A game of chance" resembles a die.
  • The map of "Anything you can do..." resembles a quaver.
  • The map of "The Race is On!" resembles an hourglass.
  • The map of "Communicating with numbers" resembles a speech bubble.
  • The examine for the pile of dream logs during the woodcutting competition is "Like a pile of memes."
  • While in Bob's dream world, players can see several other NPCs standing around: Unferth, Neite, Tristan, Camorra, and a dragonkin.

The '''Dream World''' is the realm that [[players]] are required to go to in the [[quest]]s [[Lunar Diplomacy]], [[Dream Mentor]] and [[Dragon Slayer II]]. The only known means of access is through burning [[Soaked kindling]] or using a [[Potion of Shared Dreaming]] on the [[Ceremonial brazier]] located on [[Lunar Isle]]. The history of the player is contained within the book [[my life]], which serves as an exit during Lunar Diplomacy.

[[File:Entering Dreamworld.gif|frame|A player enters the Dream World.]]

*Part of the Dream World is also visible from the first floor of the [[Stronghold of Security]], right near the entrance.
*The map of "A game of chance" resembles a die.
*The map of "Anything you can do..." resembles a quaver.
*The map of "The Race is On!" resembles an hourglass.

*While in Bob's dream world, players can see several other NPCs standing around: [[Unferth]], [[Neite]], [[Tristan]], [[Camorra]], and a [[dragonkin]].
